               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260406-310-person1667">
                  JAMES 
                  BAYLEY
               <interp inst="t18260406-310-person1667" type="surname" value="BAYLEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-310-person1667" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-310-person1667" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am in the employ of Robert Hugh Franks, a <rs id="t18260406-310-viclabel1668" type="occupation">hatter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260406-310-victim1666 t18260406-310-viclabel1668"></join>, of <placeName id="t18260406-310-crimeloc1669">Red Cross-street, Barbican</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18260406-310-crimeloc1669" type="placeName" value="Red Cross-street, Barbican"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18260406-310-crimeloc1669" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260406-310-off1666 t18260406-310-crimeloc1669"></join>. On the 18th of March, a witness, named Phelps, told me some person had taken a hat from the door - I went out and received this hat from a young man who had been in the shop buying one. The prisoner was then brought back.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260406-310-person1668">
                  WILLIAM 
                  PHELPS
               <interp inst="t18260406-310-person1668" type="surname" value="PHELPS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-310-person1668" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-310-person1668" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am fourteen years of age. I was in Red-cross-street on the 18th of March, about half-past five o'clock - I saw the prisoner take the hat from a peg - he said to me "Do not say any thing - come along with me;" he went a good way off with it - I did not see him stopped - I told the shopman of it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260406-310-person1669">
                  WILLIAM 
                  PAYNE
               <interp inst="t18260406-310-person1669" type="surname" value="PAYNE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-310-person1669" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-310-person1669" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I was sent for to take the prisoner into custody - I found him in the shop, and this sack under his arm - the hat was given me by the witness - I took him to the Compter, and found four half-crowns and 4s. 6d. in his pockets.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I went to buy a hat, and a man gave me a push, and told me to go on; I had the hat, and some men came and took me by the collar; I had the bag to go to Billingsgate to get a job - the hat was outside the door.</p>
               <p>JAMES BAYLEY re-examined. The hat was on a stand inside the door - a young man there saw him take it - he followed and brought him back.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 55.</p>
               <p>
